Europe. As an idea, it represents as a brand: it is caused by many things outside of its reach. Europe, as it was before, continuously deteriorated in idea as modern Europe becomes increasingly more distinguishable from contemporary Europe. As Freda notes: The moment has come to end with entertaining ourselves with the puppet "Europe" and chanting its name. 
To most, the Europe of now, relative to the global scale, is faint of power; even more faint in both potential and relevancy. This is the idea of Europe today. It is stagnant, invaded, and failing while the native react to the ideas and non-intricacies of whatever bourgeoisie fodder was created. Whether it is truly the better move to conform to what is to be considered reactionary ideals or to move forward with the revolutionary is a matter of hindsight and the individual's goal. Even then, this does not matter. The geographical Europe is too Americanized (as Freda would even state it is also too Sovietized) to do anything worth while. There is yet to be a rigid idea for Sovietization, even Americanization (though it could be thought of as parallel to the composite, not collection, of consumerism, individualism, and much more smaller ideas) cannot be fully defined. This composite of ideas is less of a placeholder and more of a cop-out for a nuanced and numerous collection of forces. This is one showcase. It is the showcase of how limited and narrow the scope is for the relation between the human and the worldview of the human's politic. 
Moral agency versus complacency in relation to the individual versus collective teleology in relation to the self-serving versus the giving: teleology actualized.
Moral agency versus complacency in the sedated worldview: theology.
Reaction, output of action. Systems maintain their own purpose by setting complacency, complicity generally scaled by the collectiveness of systems. No system replicated with intelligence and coherence would give real agency, organic action to the individual as the organic life is dangerous to the stable. It is not useless to analyze the collection of systems or to find the effects of the composites of systems. It is a reach to hypothesize the intention of the systems as to interpret the effects and generalities of the systems is too broad held together by the complexity of endless derivatives.

Contemporarily, Interpretation in signs no longer has worth: the hyperreal has infiltrated and blended into the social life so much that reaffirming the self and its retention of the world-view is more coherent than the actual signs of appearances and appearances themselves.
Rhetoric and ideology is packaged and orchestrated along with the simple everyday language and visual. The revelation of this to the average person creates an asymmetrical trust/distrust between ontological correlations/appearances and their own world-views.
The subject defend the retention/protention of their world and its future instead of statements with both ideal coherency and complete ontological-metaphysical correspondences, colloquially named a "fact".
This fact is not even constructed rigidly. The good rhetoric (in a Bernays' sense) is one with less nuance than it can have. The nuance is the backflow against a wave of rhetoric and it is the cloud for the world-view that is tainted by the hyperreal ideas. Simplification is then a tool for bad actors in the higher hierarchies.
The subject-subject interpretive-intent coherency drift is only small compared to the subject-culture coherency drift. The subject's habits, ideas, and sometimes existence is threatened and violated by the culture. Excessive faith and hatred amongst the subjects only fuel mechanisms to cope with these coherency drifts. This is then an opening for control of the mechanisms: amplifying, astroturfing, incentivizing.

